\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0 It is morning I was born chubby and whit body. My mother always say my age is older for fear people\uc0{\u8217}s opinion.It\uc0{\u8217}s been morning.! I run in the Streets and take Aziz\uc0{\u8217}s chador to go her Friend Mrs Soghra house, who is a janitor. in ahouse and sh is very hospitable. how sweet it is for me, a child to see them both.}}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0 Eeting the food she cooked for us was very delicious and returning home and my mother\uc0{\u8217}s surprise that I didn\uc0{\u8217}t go back to school agine!!Drinking simple tea whit them had so the meaning of life for me. Footnote (Aziz was my father\uc0{\u8217}s first wife who never became a physically a mother, but her soul is our mother forever)I was running away from going to School and my sister and me always played\uc0{\u160} the role of a sick person ,so that we didn\uc0{\u8217}t have to go to school, Just being whit Aziz ,it was enough for us. She cooks and we let us get a fresh life near her .}}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0 her presence was enough to taste life and be away from that prison for even one day. The School wanted to make something out of me that was not in me and this is the beginning of all the dualities in my being}}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0 It is not long since the morning that Aziz goes and deep pain lives in me. her chador gave the smell of the life and her hug had\uc0{\u160} had fragrance of heaven. maybe I see agine\uc0{\u160} in my dreams .her table line was endless.}}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0 She loved my mother who\uc0{\u160} was beautiful and younger than her, same of he own daughter and loved us like her own children.}}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0 It is noon now. I\uc0{\u8217}m a passionate teenager and I\uc0{\u8217}m going to the art school in pursuit of my dreams to give the new life to painting that was\uc0{\u160} companion of my years of life.}}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0 but I didn\uc0{\u8217}t see any things in that abandoned art school expect of artless teachers only the breaks time, the smell of fried buffet food, and.. The eating of the collective hands of the office staff, who were getting fatter and uglier every day. especially with their tight and long scarf, there was nothing special about it. we were forced to spend the day there with dark scarf and all our Stuffs, our work was repeated practice one skill by gouache on a card board and laughing at our own jokes. but we forgot our goal and ideals. but it left me a sweet remembered memory of my best friends that became a ointment balm for all my regrets .}}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0 little by little, my beliefs were formed my\uc0{\u160} believes ,and\uc0{\u160} I grew up with sense of spirituality and pure love To world.}}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0 It is evening, I\uc0{\u8217}m in the university class of Mrs Mahlagha, she says about Kafka , Gabriel Marquez and post modernism ..i am drunk or full of from all that information only a Few professors likes him love their work and you will benefit from their class. the rest of professors only repetition that bullshit the classic of a few centuries ago and are waiting for monthly salary, boring classes withe out any useful meaning.}}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0 A little pass of evening, a guest in the name of the love comes in my house until to be together the rest of our life. unaware\uc0{\u160} It is lust with crooked fantasy, fantasy imagination}}\par
\pard\nowidctlpar {{\cf0\f0 But I fight to believe that all of the love is avers of Hafiz \uc0{\u8217}s verses *}}\par
